The paper deals with secure transmissions in a network, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of a relay node also suggests the possibility of it falling under the networked systems (cs.NI) or systems and control (cs.SY) categories. Finally, the analysis of a queueing system could potentially place it under multimedia (cs.MM) if the data being transmitted is multimedia in nature.
